## setToArray() function

Convert a set into an array. This is not needed for modern browsers but for IE11 compatibility we use this in jsplumb.

<b>Signature:</b>

```typescript
export declare function setToArray<T>(s: Set<T>): Array<T>;
```

|  Parameter | Type | Description |
|  --- | --- | --- |
|  s | Set&lt;T&gt; |  |

<b>Returns:</b>
